The paper discusses deep generative models, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the connection between Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Variational Autoencoders (VAEs), which are both popular families of generative models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves optimization and inference, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
